  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening National and Cross-Border Humanitarian Protection Assistance, Accountability and Advocacy in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will strengthen national and cross-border protection mechanisms and provide humanitarian protection assistance for vulnerable undocumented Afghans returning from Iran and Pakistan through the four major border crossings. Through this project, IOM will strengthen gender-sensitive screening, identification and referrals for Persons with Specific Needs through capacity building for staff, government and protection actors resulting in increased referrals in Afghanistan. Further, IOM will also enhance the humanitarian returnee response to strategically prevent and respond to protection concerns such as trafficking in crisis and gender-based violence for highly vulnerable Afghans. IOM will also establish an Accountability to Affected Populations Feedback Mechanism for the overall humanitarian returnee response.</narrative>
  </description>
